<subSubSection pageId="238" pageNumber="843" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="238.[1988,2581,1201,1619]" pageId="238" pageNumber="843">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1990,2239,1314,1343]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="238" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mindorensis">Rattus mindorensis</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[2394,2513,1314,1343]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Epimys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="238" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rattus">R. rattus</taxonomicName>
species group; it is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1990,2167,1388,1422]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="238" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tiomanicus">R. tiomanicus</taxonomicName>
but not closely related to other Philippine 
<taxonomicName box="[2183,2377,1428,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="238" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">Rattus species.</taxonomicName>
It could be an insular form of 
<taxonomicName box="[2206,2382,1467,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="238" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tiomanicus">R. tiomanicus</taxonomicName>
, although this requires more research. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
