<subSubSection pageId="238" pageNumber="843" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="238.[1377,2584,1626,2488]" pageId="238" pageNumber="843">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1379,1727,2217,2251]" pageId="238" pageNumber="843">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Mindoro Mountain Rat is apparently not uncommon, but it might be threatened by deforestation dueto illegal logging on Mindoro, which generally occurs in lowlands outside of its preferred habitat. It is found in Mount Iglit National Park. Research is needed to understand its natural history, taxonomy, and conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
